+#if MORE_AI_WORK
+        // ── Upload performance: remaining opportunities ────────────────────────────────────────
+        //
+        // DONE (this session — PS-68698):
+        //   • FileOptions.Asynchronous on all FileStream opens in UploadFile + UploadAppend
+        //     — uses Windows IOCP; frees thread pool threads during disk writes.
+        //     — likely root cause of the ~4× throughput gap under concurrent load.
+        //   • Explicit 1 MB CopyToAsync buffer throughout (was ~80 KB default on block==0).
+        //   • SkipStreamBytesAsync: 8 KB → 1 MB ArrayPool buffer + CancellationToken passed through.
+        //   • [DisableRequestSizeLimit] on UploadFile + UploadAppend (Kestrel default cap: 28.6 MB).
+        //
+        // NEXT — server-side, no mobile changes required:
+        //   1. Sticky sessions at the load balancer keyed on fileGuid (or any per-upload key).
+        //      AuthenticationSystem already has a 30-second in-process user cache (USER_CACHE_TIMEOUT).
+        //      Sticky sessions mean the cache hits on every chunk after the first, eliminating the
+        //      DB round-trip per chunk on cross-server hops. Zero code change needed — LB config only.
+        //
+        //   2. HMAC-signed upload token (Application.MachineKey is already shared across the farm).
+        //      Alternative to sticky sessions: block==0 issues a signed token encoding
+        //      { fileGuid, portfolioGuid, projectId, InProgressDirectory, WebFileUploadDirectory, expiry }.
+        //      Subsequent chunks verify the HMAC locally — zero DB calls, works on any server.
+        //      Requires: mobile to read X-Upload-Token response header and echo it on subsequent blocks.
+        //      See AuthenticationFilter.PresignUrl for the existing MachineKey encrypt/decrypt pattern.
+        //
+        //   3. File pre-allocation on block==0.
+        //      If mobile passes totalSize on the first chunk, call stream.SetLength(totalSize) before
+        //      writing to avoid repeated filesystem metadata updates on each append.
+        //      Requires: new optional totalSize query parameter added to UploadAppend.
+        //
+        // NEXT — mobile changes required:
+        //   4. Verify HttpClient is a singleton (or at minimum one instance per upload session).
+        //      The LB affinity cookie lives on the HttpClientHandler's CookieContainer — recreating
+        //      the handler loses the cookie and breaks sticky sessions.
+        //      On iOS, NSUrlSessionHandler shares cookies process-wide automatically.
+        //      On Android, the same HttpClientHandler instance must be reused.
+        //      Use SocketsHttpHandler with PooledConnectionLifetime for DNS refresh without losing cookies.
+        //
+        //   5. Parallel chunk uploads.
+        //      UploadAppend already validates via offset, so out-of-order delivery is detectable.
+        //      The "multiple connections crash" experience was likely HttpClient misuse (new client per
+        //      request → socket exhaustion), not an inherent platform limit. A shared HttpClient with
+        //      2–4 concurrent POSTs to the same host is safe and would roughly multiply throughput.
+        //      HTTP/2 multiplexing over a single TCP connection is the cleanest path (one socket,
+        //      multiple concurrent streams) — requires Kestrel HTTP/2 enabled and mobile opt-in.
+        // ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+#endif
